<h2><a name='sect0' href='#toc0'>Name</a></h2>
<p>
prte_info - Display information about the PRTE installation
<h2><a name='sect1' href='#toc1'>Synopsis</a></h2>
<br>
<pre>

</pre>
<h2><a name='sect2' href='#toc2'>C]prte-info [options]R]Description</a></h2>
<p>
C]prte_infoR]
<dl>

<dt>provides detailed information
about the PRTE </dt>
<dd>installation. It can be useful for at least three common
scenarios: </dd>

<dt>1.</dt>
<dd>Checking local configuration and seeing how PRTE was installed.
</dd>

<dt>2.</dt>
<dd>Submitting bug reports / help requests to the PRTE community (see <i>https://github.com/openpmix/prte/issues.</i>
</dd>

<dt>3.</dt>
<dd>Seeing a list of installed PRTE plugins and querying what MCA parameters
they support. </dd>
</dl>

<h2><a name='sect3' href='#toc3'>Options</a></h2>
<p>
C]prte_infoR] accepts the following options:
<dl>

<dt>B]CB]-a|--allB]R]
</dt>
<dd>Show all configuration options and MCA parameters </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--archB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show architecture
PRTE was compiled on </dd>

<dt>B]CB]-c|--configB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show configuration options </dd>

<dt>B]CB]-gmca|--gmca
&lt;param&gt; &lt;value&gt;B]R] </dt>
<dd>Pass global MCA parameters that are applicable to all contexts.
</dd>

<dt>B]CB]-h|--helpB]R] </dt>
<dd>Shows help / usage message </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--hostnameB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the hostname
on which PRTE was configured and built. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--internalB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show internal
MCA parameters (not meant to be modified by users) </dd>

<dt>B]CB]-mca|--mca &lt;param&gt; &lt;value&gt;B]R]
</dt>
<dd>Pass context-specific MCA parameters; they are considered global if C]--gmcaR]
is not used and only one context is specified. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--param &lt;type&gt; &lt;component&gt;B]R]
</dt>
<dd>Show MCA parameters. The first parameter is the type of the component to
display; the second parameter is the specific component to display (or
the keyword C]allR], meaning [lq]display all components of this type[rq]).
</dd>

<dt>B]CB]--parsableB]R] </dt>
<dd>When used in conjunction with other parameters, the output
is [ga] displayed in a machine-parsable format </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--parseableB]R] </dt>
<dd>Synonym
for C]--parsableR]. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--path &lt;type&gt;B]R] </dt>
<dd>Show paths that PRTE was configured
with. Accepts the following parameters: C]prefixR], C]bindirR], C]libdirR],
C]incdirR], C]pkglibdirR], C]sysconfdirR]. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]--prettyB]R] </dt>
<dd>When used in
conjunction with other parameters, the output is displayed in &lsquo;prettyprint&rsquo;
format (default). </dd>

<dt>B]CB]-v|--version &lt;component&gt; &lt;scope&gt;B]R] </dt>
<dd>Show version of PRTE
or a component. can be the keywords C]ompiR] or C]allR], the name of a framework
(e.g., C]collR] shows all components in the C]collR] framework), or the name
of a specific component (e.g., C]pls:rshR] shows the information from the
rsh PLS component). can be one of: C]fullR], C]majorR], C]minorR], C]releaseR],
C]greekR], C]gitR]. </dd>
</dl>

<h2><a name='sect4' href='#toc4'>Examples</a></h2>

<dl>

<dt>B]CB]prte_infoB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the default output of
options and listing of installed components in a human-readable / prettyprint
format. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --parsableB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the default output of options and
listing of installed components in a machine-parsable format. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info
--param rmcast udpB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the MCA parameters of the [lq]udp[rq] RMCAST
component in a human-readable / prettyprint format. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --param
rmcast udp --parsableB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the MCA parameters of the [lq]udp[rq] RMCAST
component in a machine-parsable format. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --path bindirB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show
the [lq]bindir[rq] that PRTE was configured with. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --version
prte full --parsableB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the full version numbers of PRTE (including
the PRTE version number) in a machine-readable format. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --version
rmcast majorB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show the major version number of all RMCAST components
in a prettyprint format. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --version rmcast:tcp minorB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show
the minor version number of the TCP RMCAST component in a prettyprint format.
</dd>

<dt>B]CB]prte_info --allB]R] </dt>
<dd>Show C]allR] information about the PRTE installation,
including all components that can be found, the MCA parameters that they
support, versions of PRTE and the components, etc. </dd>
</dl>

